column5: I meant to say thanks for sharing the pics LM
WOW...big...big...big...muskies for sure!!!!!   right on
Thems gonna make some dandy fillets. How would you cook somthing that big?
Out here in East Side Scarborough, we eat em raw!!
Wow, those things would eat my PB muskie, huge fish.
wow those are certianly some huge musky.  Great pics!  Cheers!
and people laugh when we installed a harpoon on the boat.
Anyone seen the pics of thee big girls floating around some of the muskie sites the past week.Would post pics,but just recently taught to turn on a "puter" by my 6 year old son.
I saw a monster pulled out of the Bay on another musky specific board    I've only got one so far this season, but I am hoping for a few more.   Welcome aboard!

Thanks bill,the three were reportedly 55".56.5" and 58.5" and caught in Mille lacs,Vermillion and "somewhere in Canada"All the fish looked huge,really wish I could put the shots up.By the way weve been doing pretty well this year(numbers not size)Cant wait for saturday.
MN has quickly emerged as a poster child for their musky conservation efforts.  Kudos to them.  Are you listening Wisconsin?

I've been skunked this year while actually out for muskie..   Tried the French River for the opener, 3 days 14hrs a peice, not even a follow  Got back out about 3 weeks after that trip to Balsam trying to get the skunk off my back, but no luck either...  Finally 2 weeks ago while out on the Pool fishing for bass, this thing clobbers my zara spook  I am really thinking about giving the guys at Georgian Bay Musky Charters a call and booking a charter, I'd love to get a chance to hook into, or atleast see a monster.  (sorry for the crap pic, but I am still excited about it, lol)     If you want to email me the pics, I could host them for you in my Photobucket account!  Just shoot me off a PM...

Graham knows the water well.  If that's the route you wish to take, he's a good choice.  It is Gbay and there are no guarantees other than you will learn something.  He might even show you the shoal where the WR was caught.
Raf, that is what I am really after....  Catching a fish would be just a bonus.   Mouth shut, ears open

Whoa,Whoa don't go confusing me with all that fancy computer lingo and such,it took me way too long to figure out a simple post.I reached out to a friend and I am hopeing he can(link,upload,dowload,cut,paste or attach?)to this post soon.
Havn't met you but I like you sight unseen. You remind me of my dad LOL!
Well that was worth the wait. Incredible!
I    and    to all involved with those fish, inc. the fish!
Awesome pics!! Check out the guys finger in the last pic.  One for the Musky
Nice Mn fish.  thanks for sharing
I think I just wet myself
ooooooooooooooooooooh, fish porn  Sweet!!!
Those are real huge ski's..... Congratulation tonka-toy  Unbelievable Thanks for sharing Leechman
WOW!!! I don't know if I would be happy or scared to see something that size follow up my lure. Interesting how all 3 are spotted.
Leechman ,those are not my fish,I wish...I just saw them on other boards and thought i'd share.
If they were caught by trolling... they don't count!
Wow, those things are absolutely monsterous!!!!!!!!!!!!
The second fish was caught in Lake Vermillion in Northen Minnesota, and the last fish was Caught on Mille Lacs in Minnesota and it was 56.5". Thats one big mama fish!
Those are some dandy lookin MOMMAs  ....thanks for sharing those pics!!!
